-- Anglo American, BHP Billiton and MTN May Move: South Africa Equity Preview
-- Nicky Smith
-- 2010-07-09T06:19:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/anglo-american-bhp-billiton-and-mtn-may-move-south-africa-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose for a
third day, climbing 206.27, or 0.8 percent, to 27,061.19.  
 Anglo American Plc (AGL SJ): Copper in London rose on
speculation stocks of the metal have fallen to a seven-month low
which indicates increasing demand. The mining company, which
makes up about 10 percent of South Africa’s benchmark stock
index, rose 3.55 rand, or 1.3 percent, to 277 rand.  BHP Billiton
Ltd.  (BIL SJ), the world’s largest mining company, added 1.30
rand, or 0.6 percent, to 208.50 rand.  
 Vodacom Group Ltd.  (VOD SJ): South Africa’s
telecommunications regulator will accept final submissions from
companies over draft regulations on interconnection rates.
Vodacom, the largest provider of mobile-phone services to South
Africans, rose 9 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 59.59 rand.   MTN
Group Ltd.  (MTN SJ), Africa’s biggest mobile-phone company,
added 75 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 108.25 rand.  Telkom South
Africa Ltd.  (TKG SJ), Africa’s largest fixed-line operator, fell
3 cents, or 0.1 percent, to 37.66 rand.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following South
African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUK US) rose 1.2 percent to $18.35.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 0.7 percent to $40.67.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) added 1.5 percent to $55.81. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) shed 2.7 percent to $4.28. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) retreated 1.6 percent to $12.94. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) slipped 1.3 percent to $10.50. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) fell 0.2 percent to $24.30. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
jumped 3.7 percent to $4.25. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 1 percent
to $37.51.  
